Germany has announced the delivery of around 50 Gepard anti-aircraft vehicles to Ukraine after a meeting of more than 40 nations at Ramstein airbase. The nation's defence industry has been offering to sell the Gepard vehicles to Ukraine since February, but had been blocked from doing so. Mr Scholz has faced heavy criticism at home and abroad for Germany refusing to send the besieged nation heavy weapons. Polish Prime Minister Mateusz Morawiecki criticised the stance and said he would speak with the Chancellor in an effort to persuade him to send the weapons. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...  